The article is a transcript of President Joe Biden's speech at the Washington Hilton in Washington, D.C. In his speech, President Biden thanks the leaders of the Democratic National Committee and the Delaware delegation. He discusses the current state of the country, including the situation with Ukraine and rising oil prices. He highlights the achievements of the American Rescue Plan, such as the successful vaccination efforts and the positive impact on the economy. President Biden also emphasizes the importance of infrastructure and the need to invest in rebuilding America's roads, bridges, and other infrastructure. He talks about the plan to lower prescription drug prices and address the cost of childcare. He calls for corporations and the wealthy to pay their fair share of taxes and mentions the bipartisan Unity Agenda, which focuses on issues such as opioid addiction, mental health, veterans' needs, and cancer research. President Biden concludes by urging the audience to work together to bring about positive change in the country.